00:19:08.370 --> 00:19:10.560
I also like to visit
a lot of art museums,

00:19:10.560 --> 00:19:11.820
and I have a lot of art books.

00:19:11.820 --> 00:19:14.760
And I find the color
inspiration from there.

00:19:14.760 --> 00:19:18.360
And there's another, just
doodling, figuring things out,

00:19:18.360 --> 00:19:22.350
and then I painted the
table underneath there.

00:19:22.350 --> 00:19:23.970
So these are projects
for my new book.

00:19:26.620 --> 00:19:28.470
It's all real free form.

00:19:28.470 --> 00:19:31.410
I actually used my fingers
to paint a lot with,

00:19:31.410 --> 00:19:34.320
put the stripes on in different
colors and just splodge things

00:19:34.320 --> 00:19:39.262
with my fingers, and
played with the colors.

00:19:39.262 --> 00:19:40.470
There's the top of the table.

00:19:40.470 --> 00:19:43.980
And I actually made that just
by taking plates and drawing

00:19:43.980 --> 00:19:47.610
around them and figuring out the
spaces on the top of the table.

00:19:47.610 --> 00:19:49.650
Sometimes I cut
things out of paper,

00:19:49.650 --> 00:19:52.640
just like folding them to
get the shape that way.

00:19:52.640 --> 00:19:54.420
And then I trace
around it with a pencil

00:19:54.420 --> 00:19:56.350
and I paint it in by hand.

00:19:56.350 --> 00:20:00.260
And that took less than a day.

00:20:00.260 --> 00:20:02.760
It's pretty quick.

